Definition: or שֹׁד; probably from {{h7736}} (in its original sense) contracted; the breast of a woman or animal (as bulging); breast, pap, teat.
from an unused root probably meaning to eject; the fœtus (as finally expelled); that cometh of, increase.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7694}}; a (legitimate) queen; wife.
from {{h7693}}; a queen (from cohabitation); queen.
from {{h7696}}; craziness; furiously, madness.
a primitive root; to rave through insanity; (be, play the) mad (man).
from {{h7686}}; a moral mistake; error.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7689}}; large (in size, quantity or number, also adverbial); exceeding, great(-ly); many, much, sore, very.
a primitive root; to copulate with; lie with, ravish.
or שִׁגָּיֹנָה; from {{h7686}}; properly, aberration, i.e. (technically) a dithyramb or rambling poem; Shiggaion, Shigionoth.
patronymic from {{h7614}}; a Shebaite or descendant of Sheba; Sabean.
of foreign origin; Sheba, the name of three early progenitors of tribes and of an Ethiopian district; Sheba, Sabeans.
a primitive root; to transport into captivity; (bring away, carry, carry away, lead, lead away, take) captive(-s), drive (take) away.
from an unused root meaning to break up; a fragment, i.e. ruin; broken in pieces.
from {{h7604}}; a remainder or residual (surviving, final) portion; that had escaped, be left, posterity, remain(-der), remnant, residue, rest.
from {{h7605}} and {{h7725}}; a remnant will return; Shear-Jashub, the symbolic name of one of Isaiah's sons; Shear-jashub.
from {{h5375}}; an elevation or leprous scab; figuratively, elation or cheerfulness; exaltation in rank or character; be accepted, dignity, excellency, highness, raise up self, rising.
from {{h7582}}; devastation; desolation.
or שׁוּבָאֵל; from {{h7617}} (abbreviated form) or {{h7725}} and {{h410}}; captive (or returned) of God; Shebuel or Shubael, the name of two Israelites; Shebuel, Shubael.

from an unused root (probably identical with that of {{h7617}} through the idea of subdivision into flashes or streamers (compare {{h7632}}) meaning to flame; a gem (from its sparkle), probably the agate; agate.
a primitive root; to peep, i.e. glance sharply at; look (narrowly).
from {{h7679}}; (superlatively) mighty; excellent, great.

a primitive root; to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured; (cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.
from {{h7682}}; aloft; Segub, the name of two Israelites; Segub.
from {{h7683}}; a mistake or inadvertent transgression; error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly.
a primitive root; to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively); grow (up), increase.

a primitive root; to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively; defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.
a primitive root; to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology); × also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7679}}; to increase; grow, be multiplied.
probably from {{h7686}}; erring; Shage, an Israelite; Shage.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7605}}; × whatsoever more, residue, rest.
from {{h7604}}; flesh (as swelling out), as living or for food; generally food of any kind; figuratively, kindred by blood; body, flesh, food, (near) kin(-sman, -swoman), near (nigh) (of kin).
a primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. be (causatively, make) redundant; leave, (be) left, let, remain, remnant, reserve, the rest.
from {{h7604}}; a remainder; × other, remnant, residue, rest.
a primitive root; to inhale eagerly; figuratively, to cover; by implication, to be angry; also to hasten; desire (earnestly), devour, haste, pant, snuff up, swallow up.
from {{h7604}}; barm or yeast-cake (as swelling by fermentation); leaven.
a primitive root; to plunder; spoil.
feminine of {{h7607}}; female kindred by blood; near kinswomen.
the same as {{h7608}}; Sheerah, an Israelitess; Sherah.
feminine of {{h7628}}; exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively); captives(-ity).
from the same as {{h7616}}; flame (as split into tongues); spark.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7632}}; flame.
for {{h7629}}; Shobai, an Israelite; Shobai.
or שְׁבִעִי; ordinal from {{h7657}}; seventh; seventh (time).
from an unused root meaning to interweave; a netting for the hair; caul.
from the same as {{h7640}}; a track or passage-way (as if flowing along); path.
feminine of the same as {{h7629}}; captivation; Shobjah, an Israelite; Shachia (from the margin).
feminine of {{h7638}}; a net-work, i.e. (in hunting) a snare, (in architecture) a ballustrade; also a reticulated ornament to a pillar; checker, lattice, network, snare, wreath(-enwork).
from an unused root meaning to intwine; a netting (ornament to the capital of a column); net.
from {{h7618}}; exiled; captured; as noun, exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively); by extension, booty; captive(-ity), prisoners, × take away, that was taken.
from {{h7617}}; captor; Shobi, an Ammonite; Shobi.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7623}}; to adulate, i.e. adore; praise.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7626}}; a clan; tribe.

from an unused root probably meaning to branch off; a scion, i.e. (literally) a stick (for punishing, writing, fighting, ruling, walking, etc.) or (figuratively) a clan; × correction, dart, rod, sceptre, staff, tribe.
of foreign origin; Shebat, a Jewish month; Sebat.
or שָׁבֻעַ; also (feminine) שְׁבֻעָה; properly, passive participle of {{h7650}} as a denominative of {{h7651}}; literally, sevened, i.e. a week (specifically, of years); seven, week.
feminine passive participle of {{h7650}}; properly, something sworn, i.e. an oath; curse, oath, × sworn.
or שְׁבִית; from {{h7617}}; exile, concretely, prisoners; figuratively, a former state of prosperity; captive(-ity).
a primitive root; properly, to address in a loud tone, i.e. (specifically) loud; figuratively, to pacify (as if by words); commend, glory, keep in, praise, still, triumph.
from {{h7736}}; a dæmon (as malignant); devil.
dual (adverbially) of {{h7651}}; seven-times; seven(-fold, times).
prolonged for the masculine of {{h7651}}; seven; seven.

or (masculine) (שִׁבְעָה); from {{h7650}}; a primitive cardinal number; seven (as the sacred full one); also (adverbially) seven times; by implication, a week; by extension, an indefinite number; (  by) seven(-fold),-s, (-teen, -teenth), -th, times). Compare {{h7658}}.

a primitive root; properly to be complete, but used only as a denominative from {{h7651}}; to seven oneself, i.e. swear (as if by repeating a declaration seven times); adjure, charge (by an oath, with an oath), feed to the full (by mistake for {{h7646}}), take an oath, × straitly, (cause to, make to) swear.
feminine of {{h7647}}; satiety; fulness.
the same as {{h7651}}; seven; Sheba, the name of a place in Palestine, and of two Israelites; Sheba.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7651}}; seven (times).
feminine of {{h7648}}; satiety; (to have) enough, × till...be full, (un-) satiable, satisfy, × sufficiently.
multiple of {{h7651}}; seventy; seventy, threescore and ten (  -teen).
masculine of {{h7651}}; seven(-th); Shebah, a well in Palestine; Shebah.
from {{h7646}}; satisfaction (of food or [figuratively] joy); fill, full(-ness), satisfying, be satisfied.
from {{h7646}}; satiated (in a pleasant or disagreeable sense); full (of), satisfied (with).
from the same as {{h7640}}; a snail (as if floating in its own slime); snail.
or (feminine) שִׂבְמָה; probably from {{h1313}}; spice; Sebam or Sibmah, a place in Moab; Shebam, Shibmah, Sibmah.
from an unused root meaning to flow; a lady's train (as trailing after her); leg.

or (feminine) שִׁבֹּלֶת; from the same as {{h7640}}; a stream (as flowing); also an ear of grain (as growing out); by analogy, a branch; branch, channel, ear (of corn), (water-)flood, Shibboleth. Compare {{h5451}}.

or שָׂבֵעַ; a primitive root; to sate, i.e. fill to satisfaction (literally or figuratively); have enough, fill (full, self, with), be (to the) full (of), have plenty of, be satiate, satisfy (with), suffice, be weary of.
from {{h7646}}; copiousness; abundance, plenteous(-ness, -ly).
or שֶׁבְנָה; from an unused root meaning to grow; growth; Shebna or Shebnah, an Israelite; Shebna, Shebnah.
or שְׁבַנְיָהוּ; from the same as {{h7644}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has grown (i.e. prospered); Shebanjah, the name of three or four Israelites; Shebaniah.
from {{h7676}}; a sabbatism or special holiday; rest, sabbath.
intensive from {{h7673}}; intermission, i.e (specifically) the Sabbath; (  every) sabbath.
infinitive of {{h3427}}; properly, session; but used also concretely, an abode or locality; place, seat. Compare {{h3429}}.
from {{h7673}}; rest, interruption, cessation; cease, sit still, loss of time.

a primitive root; to repose, i.e. desist from exertion; used in many implied relations (causative, figurative or specific); (cause to, let, make to) cease, celebrate, cause (make) to fail, keep (sabbath), suffer to be lacking, leave, put away (down), (make to) rest, rid, still, take away.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h7660}}; to entangle, i.e. perplex; be astonished.
plural of {{h7667}}; ruins; Shebarim, a place in Palestine; Shebarim.
from {{h7665}}; rupture, i.e. a pang; figuratively, ruin; breaking, destruction.
; a primitive root; to grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (figuratively) laud; increase, magnify.
from {{h7676}}; restful; Shabbethai, the name of three Israelites; Shabbethai.
a primitive root; to interweave (colored) threads in squares; by implication (of reticulation) to inchase gems in gold; embroider, set.
from {{h7660}}; entanglement, i.e. (figuratively) perplexity; anguish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of {{h7733}}; to quit, i.e. allow to remain; leave, let alone.
erroneously שָׁבַר; (Nehemiah 2:13,15), a primitive root; to scrutinize; by implication (of watching) to expect (with hope and patience); hope, tarry, view, wait.
from {{h7663}}; expectation; hope.

a primitive root; to burst (literally or figuratively); break (down, off, in pieces, up), broken (-hearted), bring to the birth, crush, destroy, hurt, quench, × quite, tear, view (by mistake for {{h7663}}).
denominative from {{h7668}}; to deal in grain; buy, sell.

or שֵׁבֶר; from {{h7665}}; a fracture, figuratively, ruin; specifically, a solution (of a dream); affliction, breach, breaking, broken(-footed, -handed), bruise, crashing, destruction, hurt, interpretation, vexation.
the same as {{h7667}}; grain (as if broken into kernels); corn, victuals.
the same as {{h7667}}; Sheber, an Israelite; Sheber.
